This is a USB drive image for Chumby Photoframe.

1)  Delete the example images from media/images.
2)  Place your images in media/images.
3)  On a Debian-based Linux host (not your Chumby), run:

  sudo apt-get install netpbm libjpeg-progs
  make

4)  Unmount USB drive.
5)  Turn-off chumby.
6)  Plug-in USB drive.
7)  Turn-on chumby.
8)  Add Photoframe widget via http://chumby.com/.
9)  Configure Photoframe for http://localhost/image.

If you want to bootup other program
besides lighttpd,
create a file named debugchumby.foo;
debugchumby will run it.

